title: Pokemon of the Week - Tyranitar
description:
Pokemon of the week - Tyranitar

Tyranitar is a great pokemon.  I like the psuedo-legendaries.  It’s mice that they have a couple evolution stages.  The start out as the cute Larvitars.  And then they evolve into the pupitar stage which is still cute, if a little weird.  Larvitar and Tyranitar are both a pleasant shade of green.  They always reminded me of godzilla.  Especially Tyranitar.  It’s so big and scary, but you know that cute little Larvitar is still in there somewhere too!

Tyranitar is a great pokemon stat wise.  They are big and tough. Durable and hit hard.  And they have a very good move pool to choose from.  Their offensive types are really good.  Dark and Rock can do a lot of damage.  And Tyanitar almost always seems to have earthquake on it.  Sandstream is a really good ability. 

If you follow this link, serebii.net has some good ideas on how to use Tyranitar and Mega Tyranitar in competitive play.  Please follow through and check out their ideas.

summary:
Detective Pikachu was better than I expected.
Mewtwo Strikes Back was referenced which made me happy. The animations for the...
body:
Detective Pikachu was better than I expected.

Mewtwo Strikes Back was referenced which made me happy. The animations for the Pokémon were awesome! Now I really really wish Charmander was real, I’d have one as my partner in a heartbeat.

Personally, I’m not very big on detective/crime movies or shows..I didn’t much care for the story but that’s not because it wasn’t good, it’s just my personal interests. But despite that I still enjoyed it. It stayed child friendly while also being entertaining for adults. The casting was excellent. There were a few cheesy moments but honestly, it wouldn’t be Pokémon if there weren’t.

Now that they’ve done a live action Pokémon movie, I’m really hoping they do a trainer movie. If Pokémon is your thing, I’d recommend watching it!

Also, Charizard!!! I love him!!!
